% ======================================================================
%  Auburn University Research Poster -- accessible (PDF/UA-1 tagged)
%  THEME: Agriculture -- a harvest morning on the farm. Grain-cream
%  paper, deep loden-green ink, ONE barn-red accent with wheat gold in
%  support; an Alegreya serif title in the manner of a farmer's
%  almanac. Wheat-ear section markers, a farmstead vignette (sun, red
%  barn, silo, wheat spray) in the header, a faint morning sun in the
%  top-left corner, sprouting seedlings down the side margins, and
%  along the bottom a rolling patchwork of fields with contour-plough
%  furrows, hay bales, and a windmill on the horizon. The one dark
%  panel -- the theorem card -- is a plot of freshly turned soil,
%  fenced in wheat gold: the ground the main result grows from.
%
%  One clear mathematical idea: 120 x 72 cm landscape, three columns
%  with a centre-stage hierarchy -- the main theorem sits in the ONLY
%  dark panel above one strong visual (the Calabi-Yau quintic surface).
%
%  Because this poster is a plain article (not beamer), it compiles to
%  a REAL tagged, PDF/UA-1 conformant PDF: reading order, language, and
%  the logo, figures, and QR code tagged as Figures with alt text.
%
%  COMPILE WITH LuaLaTeX:
%    * Overleaf:  Menu -> Compiler -> LuaLaTeX, then Recompile.
%    * Locally:   latexmk
% ======================================================================
\NeedsTeXFormat{LaTeX2e}
\ProvidesPackage{postertheme}[2026/07/04 poster-research-agriculture poster theme]


% Fail fast, with a clear message, if the wrong engine is used.
\RequirePackage{iftex}
\RequireLuaTeX

